1. Styling Methods (Inline, Internal, External)

index.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Community Portal</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
  <style>
    body {
      background-color: #f0f8ff;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1 style="color: red;">Local Community Event</h1>
  <h2 id="mainHeader">Upcoming Events</h2>
  <div class="eventCard">Sample Event Card</div>
</body>
</html>
styles.css
/* Header styles */
#mainHeader {
  font-size: 28px;
  color: #333;
}

/* Event card styles */
.eventCard {
  background-color: #e6f7ff;
  padding: 15px;
  margin: 10px;
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
}


2. CSS Syntax and Comments

/* Style for main CTA button */
.cta-button {
  background-color: #007BFF;
  color: white;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  font-weight: bold;
}


3. Selectors Playground

* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}

h2 {
  font-size: 24px;
  color: darkblue;
}

#mainHeader {
  background-color: #ccc;
  padding: 10px;
}

.eventCard {
  border: 1px solid #444;
  margin: 10px;
  padding: 10px;
}

h3, p {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

4. Color & Background Styling

body {
  background: url('bg.jpg') no-repeat center center fixed;
  background-color: #cccccc;
  background-size: cover;
}

.header {
  background: linear-gradient(to right, #003366, #336699);
  color: white;
}

.text-hex {
  color: #FF5733;
}

.text-rgba {
  background-color: rgba(0, 128, 0, 0.3);
}


5. Typography: Fonts and Text
index.html

<head>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>

styles.css
body {
  font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
}

.title {
  font-size: 32px;
  font-style: italic;
  font-weight: 600;
}

.description {
  text-align: justify;
  text-transform: capitalize;
  letter-spacing: 1px;
  line-height: 1.8;
}


6. Link and List Styling

a:link {
  color: #0066cc;
}

a:hover {
  color: #ff6600;
}

a:active {
  color: red;
}

a:visited {
  color: purple;
}

ul.nav {
  list-style-type: none;
  list-style-position: inside;
  padding-left: 0;
}

ul.nav li {
  margin: 10px 0;
  padding: 5px;
}

7. Table Styling
table {
  border-collapse: collapse;
  width: 100%;
}

th, td {
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  padding: 8px;
  text-align: center;
}

tr:nth-child(even) {
  background-color: #f9f9f9;
}

8.Box Model & Layout Control
.eventCard {
  margin: 20px;
  padding: 15px;
  border: 2px solid #333;
}

input:focus {
  outline: 2px solid #007BFF;
}

/* For visibility comparison */
.hidden {
  visibility: hidden;
}

.none {
  display: none;
}

9. Multiple Columns in Text

.news-article {
  column-count: 2;
  column-gap: 30px;
  column-rule: 1px solid gray;
}

10. Responsive Web Design with Media Queries

@media screen and (max-width: 768px) {
  nav ul {
    display: block;
  }

  nav ul li {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  body {
    font-size: 14px;
  }
}

.container {
  width: 90%;
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: auto;
}

.flex-layout {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 20px;
}
